  "title": "[Documentation] hierarchicalMenu `cssClasses.depth` option seems wrong",
  "body": "<img width=\"576\" alt=\"capture d ecran 2016-05-22 a 22 43 02\" src=\"https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/314079/15461303/c160f346-206e-11e6-9548-0607b2812a8d.png\">\n\nProbably a bad copy/paste. There's no \"depth\" element, but a class to differentiate the different depths of items in the hierarchy, right?\n\nProposition:\n\n> CSS class to add to each item element to denote its depth. The actual level will be appended to the given class name (ie. if `\"depth\"` is given, the widget will add `\"depth0\"`, `\"depth1\"`, ... according to the level of each item).\n",
